        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:11PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 211 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Blood Mountain Shelter,
or 9 miles south of Blairsville, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Unicoi State Park, Owltown, Whitley Gap Shelter, Blue Mountain
Shelter, Vogel State Park, Brasstown Bald, Track Rock, Anna Ruby
Falls, Turners Corner, Woods Hole Shelter, Blood Mountain Shelter,
and Low Gap Shelter.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
